.SH "NAME"
xdr_init_encode \- Initialize a struct xdr_stream for sending data\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ xdr_init_encode('u
.BI "void xdr_init_encode(struct\ xdr_stream\ *\ " "xdr" ", struct\ xdr_buf\ *\ " "buf" ", __be32\ *\ " "p" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIxdr\fR
.RS 4
pointer to xdr_stream struct
.RE
.PP
\fIbuf\fR
.RS 4
pointer to XDR buffer in which to encode data
.RE
.PP
\fIp\fR
.RS 4
current pointer inside XDR buffer
.RE
.SH "NOTE"
.PP
at the moment the RPC client only passes the length of our scratch buffer in the xdr_buf\*(Aqs header kvec\&. Previously this meant we needed to call
\fBxdr_adjust_iovec\fR
after encoding the data\&. With the new scheme, the xdr_stream manages the details of the buffer length, and takes care of adjusting the kvec length for us\&.
